  "prompt": "Donated blood is mixed with sodium citrate?",
  "response": "Yes, donated blood is typically mixed with an anticoagulant solution that contains sodium citrate. This helps to prevent the blood from clotting during storage and transfusion. The most commonly used anticoagulant for blood donation is CPD (citrate-phosphate-dextrose), which includes sodium citrate as one of its components.",
